    ("Weather satellites provide:", ["only visible-light photographs during daytime", "continuous observations of clouds, water vapor, temperature profiles, wind fields, and surface conditions using multiple sensors across visible, infrared, and microwave wavelengths", "only precipitation measurements", "only ground-level temperature data"], 1, "Geostationary and polar-orbiting complement each other."),
